/*Problem Description:
You are given a non-negative integer n. Write a recursive function to compute its factorial. 
The factorial of a number n is defined as: 
1. n! = n × (n-1) × (n-2) × ... × 1 
2. By definition, 0! = 1 
Your function must correctly handle the edge case when n = 0. Also consider what should 
happen if a negative number is passed. 
Requirements:
1. Use recursion only (no loops). 
2. Clearly define the base case. 
3. Ensure your function does not cause infinite recursion*/

package com.pgcp.ads.assignment1;

public class FactorialWithEdgeCaseHandling {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int n = 4;

		System.out.println(factorial(n));

	}

	private static int factorial(int n) {
		int result = 0;
		if (n == 1) {
			return 1;	 
		}else {
			result = n * (factorial(n - 1));
		}
		return result;
	}
}

